<subSubSection id="C37F6544FF8AFFBADBA4FF6A2F3A91AE" box="[151,352,186,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA36CFFF8AFFBADBA4FF6A2F3A91AE" blockId="14.[151,455,151,212]" box="[151,352,186,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="41">
(
<figureCitation id="135E2A4AFF8AFFBADBACFF6A2F5D91AE" box="[159,263,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,244,1849,1870]" captionTargetBox="[266,1308,156,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-155@5.[266,1308,156,1834]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Neozygina dorsal habitus. A, N. abluta, holotype female; B, N. apacha; C, N. balli, holotype male; D, N. ceonothana; E, N. davisi; F, N. huachucana, holotype male; G, N. penapacha, holotype male; H, N. quadricornis; I, N. antlera, holotype male; J, N. chiapensis, holotype male; K, N. hondurensis, holotype male; L, N. mandibulata, holotype male; M, N. obsoleta, holotype male; N, N. potosiensis, holotype male; O, N. sonorensis, holotype male; P, N. sordida, holotype male; Q, N. veracruzensis, holotype male; R, N. zapatai, holotype male; S, N. argentiniensis, holotype male; T, N. abancayensis, holotype male; U, N. asymmetrica, holotype male; V, N. expanda, holotype male; W, N. forcipata, holotype male; X, N. retrorsa, holotype male." pageId="14" pageNumber="41">Figs. 1X</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135E2A4AFF8AFFBADA27FF6A2F0291AE" box="[276,344,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[278,1261,789,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-314@14.[275,1312,789,1539]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. New South American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, N), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, J, L, O) and posterior (C, F, I, K, M, P) views. A–C, N. abancayensis; D–F, N. argentiniensis; G–I, N. asymmetrica; J–K, N. expanda; L–M, N. forcipata; N–P, N. retrorsa." pageId="14" pageNumber="41">4N–P</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6544FF8AFFBADBA4FEDA2F1E90BE" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA36CFFF8AFFBADBA4FEDA2F1E90BE" blockId="14.[151,1436,266,732]" pageId="14" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8AFFBADBA4FEDA2F4D905E" bold="true" box="[151,279,266,292]" pageId="14" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length of male 
<quantity id="4C9D9B2AFF8AFFBADAE5FEDA2C69905E" box="[470,563,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
, female 
<quantity id="4C9D9B2AFF8AFFBAD9A7FEDA2CAA905E" box="[660,752,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
. Closely resembling 
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8AFFBAD8D7FEDA2AE89059" box="[996,1202,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4CFF8AFFBAD8D7FEDA2AF49059" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2007" box="[996,1198,266,291]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentiniensis">N. argentiniensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but differing as follows: male pygofer (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4AFF8AFFBADAA5FEE22FAC9036" box="[406,502,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[278,1261,789,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-314@14.[275,1312,789,1539]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. New South American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, N), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, J, L, O) and posterior (C, F, I, K, M, P) views. A–C, N. abancayensis; D–F, N. argentiniensis; G–I, N. asymmetrica; J–K, N. expanda; L–M, N. forcipata; N–P, N. retrorsa." pageId="14" pageNumber="41">Fig. 4N</figureCitation>
) with ventral spine more elongate, strongly curved dorsad and only slightly mesad; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4AFF8AFFBADA5DFE8A2FAE900E" box="[366,500,346,372]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[278,1261,789,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-314@14.[275,1312,789,1539]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. New South American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, N), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, J, L, O) and posterior (C, F, I, K, M, P) views. A–C, N. abancayensis; D–F, N. argentiniensis; G–I, N. asymmetrica; J–K, N. expanda; L–M, N. forcipata; N–P, N. retrorsa." pageId="14" pageNumber="41">Figs. 4O, P</figureCitation>
) without basal processes, shaft very narrowly U-shaped in lateral view, apex in posterior view with pair of short forcipate distal processes and pair of retrorse lateral preapical spines, sinuate in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
