<paragraph id="8BDA36CFFF8AFFBADBF5FD4A2AEC93A6" blockId="14.[151,1436,266,732]" pageId="14" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8AFFBADBF5FD4A2F5D93CE" bold="true" box="[198,263,666,692]" pageId="14" pageNumber="41">Note.</emphasis>
This species differs from other South American 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4CFF8AFFBAD861FD4A2D9493C9" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2006" box="[850,974,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neozygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EADDFF8AFFBAD861FD4A2D9493C9" box="[850,974,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="41">Neozygina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the aedeagus without paired basal processes and a distal pair of retrorse spines, upon which the specific name is based.
</paragraph>
